lickable prototypes: no design or coding skills required.", "link": "https://the-decoder.com/google-labs-turns-stitch-into-a-full-ai-design-platform-that-converts-plain-text-into-user-interfaces/", "source": "The Decoder", "image": null, "score": 1}, {"id": "https://the-decoder.com/?p=33348", "title": "Apple reportedly blocks vibe-coding apps from publishing updates", "summary": "Apple is preventing popular vibe-coding apps like Replit and Vibecode from releasing new versions. The company points to existing guidelines, but the move targets potential competition to its own ecosystem.", "link": "https://the-decoder.com/apple-reportedly-blocks-vibe-coding-apps-from-publishing-updates/", "source": "The Decoder", "image": null, "score": 1}, {"id": "https://the-decoder.com/?p=33349", "title": "Pentagon plans to let AI companies train models on classified data", "summary": "The US Department of War is working to set up secure environments where AI companies can train their models on classified data. Until now, models were only allowed to read classified data, not learn from it.", "link": "https://the-decoder.com/pentagon-plans-to-let-ai-companies-train-models-on-classified-data/", "source": "The Decoder", "image": null, "score": 1}], "today_tech": [{"id": "oai:arXiv.org:2603.16923v1", "title": "Beyond Deep Learning: Speech Segmentation and Phone Classification with Neural Assemblies", "summary": "Abstract: Deep learning dominates speech processing but relies on massive datasets, global backpropagation-guided weight updates, and produces entangled representations. Assembly Calculus (AC), which models sparse neuronal assemblies via Hebbian plasticity and winner-take-all competition, offers a b...", "link": "https://arxiv.org/abs/2603.16923", "source": "arXiv Audio & Speech", "image": "https://arxiv.org/html/2603.16923v1/2603.16923v1/figures/AC_fundamentals.png", "score": 15}, {"id": "oai:arXiv.org:2603.16941v1", "title": "The Voice Behind the Words: Quantifying Intersectional Bias in SpeechLLMs", "summary": "Abstract: Speech Large Language Models (SpeechLLMs) process spoken input directly, retaining cues such as accent and perceived gender that were previously removed in cascaded pipelines. This introduces speaker identity dependent variation in responses. We present a large-scale intersectional evaluat...", "link": "https://arxiv.org/abs/2603.16941", "source": "arXiv Audio & Speech", "image": "https://arxiv.org/html/2603.16941v1/2603.16941v1/x1.png", "score": 13}, {"id": "oai:arXiv.org:2603.16922v1", "title": "Learnable Pulse Accumulation for On-Device Speech Recognition: How Much Attention Do You Need?", "summary": "Abstract: Self-attention scales quadratically with sequence length, limiting transformer-based speech models on edge devices. We introduce the Learnable Pulse Accumulator (LPA), an O(n) replacement that substitutes key-query dot products with learned gating functions: content-dependent rectangular p...", "link": "https://arxiv.org/abs/2603.16922", "source": "arXiv Audio & Speech", "image": "https://arxiv.org/html/2603.16922v1/2603.16922v1/x1.png", "score": 11}, {"id": "oai:arXiv.org:2603.16920v1", "title": "Synthetic Data Domain Adaptation for ASR via LLM-based Text and Phonetic Respelling Augmentation", "summary": "Abstract: End-to-end automatic speech recognition often degrades on domain-specific data due to scarce in-domain resources. We propose a synthetic-data-based domain adaptation framework with two contributions: (1) a large language model (LLM)-based text augmentation pipeline with a filtering strateg...", "link": "https://arxiv.org/abs/2603.16920", "source": "arXiv Audio & Speech", "image": "https://arxiv.org/html/2603.16920v1/2603.16920v1/x1.png", "score": 10}, {"id": "oai:arXiv.org:2603.17169v1", "title": "How Clued up are LLMs? Evaluating Multi-Step Deductive Reasoning in a Text-Based Game Environment", "summary": "Abstract: Deducing whodunit proves challenging for LLM agents. In this paper, we implement a text-based multi-agent version of the classic board game Clue as a rule-based testbed for evaluating multi-step deductive reasoning, with six agents drawn from GPT-4o-mini and Gemini-2.5-Flash. We further in...", "link": "https://arxiv.org/abs/2603.17169", "source": "arXiv AI", "image": "https://arxiv.org/html/2603.17169v1/2603.17169v1/figures/clue_diagram_v2.png", "score": 9}]}